obo:GO_0099524  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4628  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2A, S2. Immunofluorescence and confocal microscopy with antibodies to the GABAAR g2 subunit and antibodies specific to KIF5B show that a proportion of KIF5B staining colocalized with GABAAR clusters in the neuronal somata and dendrites of cultured hippocampal and cortical neurons.\n\nFigure 2L,O, 3A-D. Pulldown assays with antibodies, GST fusion proteins, and mutated domains as controls, reveal HAP1 interacts with KIF5B. Further, mutated KIF5B effects GABAARs insertion into the surface membrane through the KIF5-HAP1 complex (Fig 3H, 4F). This supports the KIF5B-GABAAR colocalization observed earlier.. Experimental description: M&M: Adult Sprague-Dawley rats\n\nAffinity purifications, using GST-fusion proteins purified from E. coli, were performed as described in a number of previous studies (see refs (Kittler et al., 2005; Kittler et al., 2000a)).\n\nKIF5 immunogold was only performed for KIF5C." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-05-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4628" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

